    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-04-14T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-04-14T14:00:00-05:00" n="240"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3004: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Feely</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-14T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 14, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Your 30, April 10, 9 p.m. Would it be possible to find a way out by
                    incorporating in a new proposal the features of the Neutrals’ proposal of
                    December 15th last<note n="84" xml:id="d240fn84">
                        <ref target="frus1932v05#pg_126">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1932, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p. 126</ref>.</note> for determination of
                    the Chaco by a board of geographers, to be followed by an arbitral settlement of
                    the matter and the provision in the Mendoza formula for the withdrawal of troops
                    to Ballivian and Bobore?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
